peopleAlsoAsk.question: Is there a market for old dishes?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Vintage china, glassware and flatware can bring several hundred to thousands of dollars. But demand for most formal dinnerware continues to decrease, so make a plan now to sell it before the end of the year.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What type of dishes are worth money?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet:
China isn't the only type of vintage dishware worth money. Blue and white transferware dishes, especially older ones, can be worth a few extra dollars to collectors. Flow blue pieces can be priced depending on their style - Oriental, romantic, or floral - and their age and condition.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How do you know if a plate is worth money?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: One of the most important factors that determine the value of collectible plates is their rarity. The rarer a plate is, the more valuable it becomes. Rarity can be determined by various factors such as limited production runs, discontinued patterns or designs, or plates made by renowned manufacturers.
